explanation: This solution works by first checking if the two strings are equal or have different lengths. If they are equal, it returns true. If they have different lengths, it returns false. Then it finds the first position where the two strings differ. If the first differing position is at the decimal point, it checks if the rest of the strings are equal. If the first differing position is at the decimal point and there is a repeating part, it checks if the repeating parts are equal. If none of the above conditions are met, it returns false. This solution has a high efficiency because it only needs to traverse the strings once.

